main event: A witness in Moorhead, Minnesota reported seeing an unidentified object in the sky on October 29, 1962.
interesting points: The witness could not describe the object, only that it was comparable to a flame and a lot of smoke.
The object was believed to be in the east-northeast flight path.
The total duration of the sighting was assumed to include the time it took to notify investigating officers.
No decay of light or sound was reported.
The data was not sufficient for a full evaluation, and the conclusion was that it could possibly be a meteor, astronomical object, or an aircraft.
sighted object: an unidentified object described as comparable to a flame and a lot of smoke
